body:
Unable to use spliceRows() , spliceColumns().
Getting following error : 
`TypeError: worksheet.spliceRows is not a function`

code : 
```
    var options = {
        filename: './streamed-workbook.xlsx',
        useStyles: true,
        useSharedStrings: true
    };
    var workbook = new Excel.stream.xlsx.WorkbookWriter(options);

    var worksheet = workbook.addWorksheet('My Sheet');

    worksheet.addRow([1, 2, 3]);
    worksheet.addRow([4, 5, 6]);


    var newRowValues = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];
    worksheet.spliceRows(1, 1, newRowValues);

    workbook.commit()
```


Env - Nodejs 8.x

comments.body:
I know it's crappy, but I got it working with this

```js
const standardWorksheet = require("exceljs/lib/doc/worksheet");

Object.assign(streamWorksheet, {
    spliceColumns: standardWorksheet.prototype.spliceColumns,
    spliceRows: standardWorksheet.prototype.spliceRows
});
```
